USER     def get_ident_filename_matches(self, idents):
USER         all_fnames = defaultdict(set)
USER         for fname in self.get_all_relative_files():
USER             # Skip empty paths or just '.'
USER             if not fname or fname == ".":
USER                 continue
USER 
USER             try:
USER                 # Handle dotfiles properly
USER                 path = Path(fname)
USER                 base = path.stem.lower()  # Use stem instead of with_suffix("").name
USER                 if len(base) >= 5:
USER                     all_fnames[base].add(fname)
USER             except ValueError:
USER                 # Skip paths that can't be processed
USER                 continue
USER 
USER         matches = set()
USER         for ident in idents:
USER             if len(ident) < 5:
USER                 continue
USER             matches.update(all_fnames[ident.lower()])
USER 
USER         return matches
USER 
USER     def get_repo_map(self, force_refresh=False):
USER         if not self.repo_map:
USER             return
USER 
USER         cur_msg_text = self.get_cur_message_text()
USER         mentioned_fnames = self.get_file_mentions(cur_msg_text)
USER         mentioned_idents = self.get_ident_mentions(cur_msg_text)
USER 
USER         mentioned_fnames.update(self.get_ident_filename_matches(mentioned_idents))
USER 
USER         all_abs_files = set(self.get_all_abs_files())
USER         repo_abs_read_only_fnames = set(self.abs_read_only_fnames) & all_abs_files
USER         chat_files = set(self.abs_fnames) | repo_abs_read_only_fnames
USER         other_files = all_abs_files - chat_files
USER 
USER         repo_content = self.repo_map.get_repo_map(
USER             chat_files,
USER             other_files,
USER             mentioned_fnames=mentioned_fnames,
USER             mentioned_idents=mentioned_idents,
USER             force_refresh=force_refresh,
USER         )
USER 
USER         # fall back to global repo map if files in chat are disjoint from rest of repo
USER         if not repo_content:
USER             repo_content = self.repo_map.get_repo_map(
USER                 set(),
USER                 all_abs_files,
USER                 mentioned_fnames=mentioned_fnames,
USER                 mentioned_idents=mentioned_idents,
USER             )
USER 
USER         # fall back to completely unhinted repo
USER         if not repo_content:
USER             repo_content = self.repo_map.get_repo_map(
USER                 set(),
USER                 all_abs_files,
USER             )
USER 
USER         return repo_content

USER     def get_images_message(self, fnames):
USER         supports_images = self.main_model.info.get("supports_vision")
USER         supports_pdfs = self.main_model.info.get("supports_pdf_input") or self.main_model.info.get(
USER             "max_pdf_size_mb"
USER         )
USER 
USER         # https://github.com/BerriAI/litellm/pull/6928
USER         supports_pdfs = supports_pdfs or "claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022" in self.main_model.name
USER 
USER         if not (supports_images or supports_pdfs):
USER             return None
USER 
USER         image_messages = []
USER         for fname in fnames:
USER             if not is_image_file(fname):
USER                 continue
USER 
USER             mime_type, _ = mimetypes.guess_type(fname)
USER             if not mime_type:
USER                 continue
USER 
USER             with open(fname, "rb") as image_file:
USER                 encoded_string = base64.b64encode(image_file.read()).decode("utf-8")
USER             image_url = f"data:{mime_type};base64,{encoded_string}"
USER             rel_fname = self.get_rel_fname(fname)
USER 
USER             if mime_type.startswith("image/") and supports_images:
USER                 image_messages += [
USER                     {"type": "text", "text": f"Image file: {rel_fname}"},
USER                     {"type": "image_url", "image_url": {"url": image_url, "detail": "high"}},
USER                 ]
USER             elif mime_type == "application/pdf" and supports_pdfs:
USER                 image_messages += [
USER                     {"type": "text", "text": f"PDF file: {rel_fname}"},
USER                     {"type": "image_url", "image_url": image_url},
USER                 ]
USER 
USER         if not image_messages:
USER             return None
USER 
USER         return {"role": "user", "content": image_messages}

USER     def run(self, with_message=None, preproc=True):

USER             while True:

USER     def run_one(self, user_message, preproc):
USER         self.init_before_message()
USER 
USER         if preproc:
USER             message = self.preproc_user_input(user_message)
USER         else:
USER             message = user_message
USER 
USER         while message:
USER             self.reflected_message = None
USER             list(self.send_message(message))
USER 
USER             if not self.reflected_message:
USER                 break
USER 
USER             if self.num_reflections >= self.max_reflections:
USER                 self.io.tool_warning(f"Only {self.max_reflections} reflections allowed, stopping.")
USER                 return
USER 
USER             self.num_reflections += 1
USER             message = self.reflected_message
USER 
USER     def check_and_open_urls(self, exc, friendly_msg=None):
USER         """Check exception for URLs, offer to open in a browser, with user-friendly error msgs."""
USER         text = str(exc)
USER 
USER         if friendly_msg:
USER             self.io.tool_warning(text)
USER             self.io.tool_error(f"{friendly_msg}")
USER         else:
USER             self.io.tool_error(text)
USER 
USER         url_pattern = re.compile(r"(https?://[^\s/$.?#].[^\s]*)")
USER         urls = list(set(url_pattern.findall(text)))  # Use set to remove duplicates
USER         for url in urls:
USER             url = url.rstrip(".',\"")
USER             self.io.offer_url(url)
USER         return urls
USER 
USER     def check_for_urls(self, inp: str) -> List[str]:
USER         """Check input for URLs and offer to add them to the chat."""
USER         if not self.detect_urls:
USER             return inp
USER 
USER         url_pattern = re.compile(r"(https?://[^\s/$.?#].[^\s]*[^\s,.])")
USER         urls = list(set(url_pattern.findall(inp)))  # Use set to remove duplicates
USER         group = ConfirmGroup(urls)
USER         for url in urls:
USER             if url not in self.rejected_urls:
USER                 url = url.rstrip(".',\"")
USER                 if self.io.confirm_ask(
USER                     "Add URL to the chat?", subject=url, group=group, allow_never=True
USER                 ):
USER                     inp += "\n\n"
USER                     inp += self.commands.cmd_web(url, return_content=True)
USER                 else:
USER                     self.rejected_urls.add(url)
USER 
USER         return inp
USER

USER     def summarize_worker(self):

USER     def warm_cache(self, chunks):
USER         if not self.add_cache_headers:
USER             return
USER         if not self.num_cache_warming_pings:
USER             return
USER 
USER         delay = 5 * 60 - 5
USER         self.next_cache_warm = time.time() + delay
USER         self.warming_pings_left = self.num_cache_warming_pings
USER         self.cache_warming_chunks = chunks
USER 
USER         if self.cache_warming_thread:
USER             return
USER 
USER         def warm_cache_worker():
USER             while True:
USER                 time.sleep(1)
USER                 if self.warming_pings_left <= 0:
USER                     continue
USER                 now = time.time()
USER                 if now < self.next_cache_warm:
USER                     continue
USER 
USER                 self.warming_pings_left -= 1
USER                 self.next_cache_warm = time.time() + delay
USER 
USER                 kwargs = dict(self.main_model.extra_params) or dict()
USER                 kwargs["max_tokens"] = 1
USER 
USER                 try:
USER                     completion = litellm.completion(
USER                         model=self.main_model.name,
USER                         messages=self.cache_warming_chunks.cacheable_messages(),
USER                         stream=False,
USER                         **kwargs,
USER                     )
USER                 except Exception as err:
USER                     self.io.tool_warning(f"Cache warming error: {str(err)}")
USER                     continue
USER 
USER                 cache_hit_tokens = getattr(
USER                     completion.usage, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens", 0
USER                 ) or getattr(completion.usage, "cache_read_input_tokens", 0)
USER 
USER                 if self.verbose:
USER                     self.io.tool_output(f"Warmed {format_tokens(cache_hit_tokens)} cached tokens.")
USER 
USER         self.cache_warming_thread = threading.Timer(0, warm_cache_worker)
USER         self.cache_warming_thread.daemon = True
USER         self.cache_warming_thread.start()
USER 
USER         return chunks
USER 
USER     def send_message(self, inp):
USER         self.event("message_send_starting")
USER 
USER         self.cur_messages += [
USER             dict(role="user", content=inp),
USER         ]
USER 
USER         chunks = self.format_messages()
USER         messages = chunks.all_messages()
USER         self.warm_cache(chunks)
USER 
USER         if self.verbose:
USER             utils.show_messages(messages, functions=self.functions)
USER 
USER         self.multi_response_content = ""
USER         if self.show_pretty() and self.stream:
USER             self.mdstream = self.io.get_assistant_mdstream()
USER         else:
USER             self.mdstream = None
USER 
USER         retry_delay = 0.125
USER 
USER         litellm_ex = LiteLLMExceptions()
USER

USER         interrupted = False

USER             while True:
USER                 try:
USER                     yield from self.send(messages, functions=self.functions)
USER                     break

USER                     if ex_info.name == "ContextWindowExceededError":
USER                         exhausted = True

USER                     should_retry = ex_info.retry

USER     def get_file_mentions(self, content):
USER         words = set(word for word in content.split())
USER 
USER         # drop sentence punctuation from the end
USER         words = set(word.rstrip(",.!;:?") for word in words)
USER 
USER         # strip away all kinds of quotes
USER         quotes = "".join(['"', "'", "`"])
USER         words = set(word.strip(quotes) for word in words)
USER 
USER         addable_rel_fnames = self.get_addable_relative_files()
USER 
USER         # Get basenames of files already in chat or read-only
USER         existing_basenames = {os.path.basename(f) for f in self.get_inchat_relative_files()} | {
USER             os.path.basename(self.get_rel_fname(f)) for f in self.abs_read_only_fnames
USER         }
USER 
USER         mentioned_rel_fnames = set()
USER         fname_to_rel_fnames = {}
USER         for rel_fname in addable_rel_fnames:
USER             # Skip files that share a basename with files already in chat
USER             if os.path.basename(rel_fname) in existing_basenames:
USER                 continue
USER 
USER             normalized_rel_fname = rel_fname.replace("\\", "/")
USER             normalized_words = set(word.replace("\\", "/") for word in words)
USER             if normalized_rel_fname in normalized_words:
USER                 mentioned_rel_fnames.add(rel_fname)
USER 
USER             fname = os.path.basename(rel_fname)
USER 
USER             # Don't add basenames that could be plain words like "run" or "make"
USER             if "/" in fname or "\\" in fname or "." in fname or "_" in fname or "-" in fname:
USER                 if fname not in fname_to_rel_fnames:
USER                     fname_to_rel_fnames[fname] = []
USER                 fname_to_rel_fnames[fname].append(rel_fname)
USER 
USER         for fname, rel_fnames in fname_to_rel_fnames.items():
USER             if len(rel_fnames) == 1 and fname in words:
USER                 mentioned_rel_fnames.add(rel_fnames[0])
USER 
USER         return mentioned_rel_fnames
USER 
USER     def check_for_file_mentions(self, content):
USER         mentioned_rel_fnames = self.get_file_mentions(content)
USER 
USER         new_mentions = mentioned_rel_fnames - self.ignore_mentions
USER 
USER         if not new_mentions:
USER             return
USER 
USER         added_fnames = []
USER         group = ConfirmGroup(new_mentions)
USER         for rel_fname in sorted(new_mentions):
USER             if self.io.confirm_ask(f"Add {rel_fname} to the chat?", group=group, allow_never=True):
USER                 self.add_rel_fname(rel_fname)
USER                 added_fnames.append(rel_fname)
USER             else:
USER                 self.ignore_mentions.add(rel_fname)
USER 
USER         if added_fnames:
USER             return prompts.added_files.format(fnames=", ".join(added_fnames))
USER

USER     def show_send_output(self, completion):
USER         if self.verbose:
USER             print(completion)
USER 
USER         if not completion.choices:
USER             self.io.tool_error(str(completion))
USER             return
USER 
USER         show_func_err = None
USER         show_content_err = None
USER         try:
USER             if completion.choices[0].message.tool_calls:
USER                 self.partial_response_function_call = (
USER                     completion.choices[0].message.tool_calls[0].function
USER                 )
USER         except AttributeError as func_err:
USER             show_func_err = func_err
USER 
USER         try:
USER             self.partial_response_content = completion.choices[0].message.content or ""
USER         except AttributeError as content_err:
USER             show_content_err = content_err
USER 
USER         resp_hash = dict(
USER             function_call=str(self.partial_response_function_call),
USER             content=self.partial_response_content,
USER         )
USER         resp_hash = hashlib.sha1(json.dumps(resp_hash, sort_keys=True).encode())
USER         self.chat_completion_response_hashes.append(resp_hash.hexdigest())
USER 
USER         if show_func_err and show_content_err:
USER             self.io.tool_error(show_func_err)
USER             self.io.tool_error(show_content_err)
USER             raise Exception("No data found in LLM response!")
USER 
USER         show_resp = self.render_incremental_response(True)
USER         self.io.assistant_output(show_resp, pretty=self.show_pretty())
USER 
USER         if (
USER             hasattr(completion.choices[0], "finish_reason")
USER             and completion.choices[0].finish_reason == "length"
USER         ):
USER             raise FinishReasonLength()
USER 
USER     def show_send_output_stream(self, completion):
USER         for chunk in completion:
USER             if len(chunk.choices) == 0:
USER                 continue
USER 
USER             if (
USER                 hasattr(chunk.choices[0], "finish_reason")
USER                 and chunk.choices[0].finish_reason == "length"
USER             ):
USER                 raise FinishReasonLength()
USER 
USER             try:
USER                 func = chunk.choices[0].delta.function_call
USER                 # dump(func)
USER                 for k, v in func.items():
USER                     if k in self.partial_response_function_call:
USER                         self.partial_response_function_call[k] += v
USER                     else:
USER                         self.partial_response_function_call[k] = v
USER             except AttributeError:
USER                 pass
USER 
USER             try:
USER                 text = chunk.choices[0].delta.content
USER                 if text:
USER                     self.partial_response_content += text
USER             except AttributeError:
USER                 text = None
USER 
USER             if self.show_pretty():
USER                 self.live_incremental_response(False)
USER             elif text:
USER                 try:
USER                     sys.stdout.write(text)
USER                 except UnicodeEncodeError:
USER                     # Safely encode and decode the text
USER                     safe_text = text.encode(sys.stdout.encoding, errors="backslashreplace").decode(
USER                         sys.stdout.encoding
USER                     )
USER                     sys.stdout.write(safe_text)
USER                 sys.stdout.flush()
USER                 yield text
USER

USER     def calculate_and_show_tokens_and_cost(self, messages, completion=None):
USER         prompt_tokens = 0
USER         completion_tokens = 0
USER         cache_hit_tokens = 0
USER         cache_write_tokens = 0
USER 
USER         if completion and hasattr(completion, "usage") and completion.usage is not None:
USER             prompt_tokens = completion.usage.prompt_tokens
USER             completion_tokens = completion.usage.completion_tokens
USER             cache_hit_tokens = getattr(completion.usage, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens", 0) or getattr(
USER                 completion.usage, "cache_read_input_tokens", 0
USER             )
USER             cache_write_tokens = getattr(completion.usage, "cache_creation_input_tokens", 0)
USER 
USER             if hasattr(completion.usage, "cache_read_input_tokens") or hasattr(
USER                 completion.usage, "cache_creation_input_tokens"
USER             ):
USER                 self.message_tokens_sent += prompt_tokens
USER                 self.message_tokens_sent += cache_write_tokens
USER             else:
USER                 self.message_tokens_sent += prompt_tokens
USER 
USER         else:
USER             prompt_tokens = self.main_model.token_count(messages)
USER             completion_tokens = self.main_model.token_count(self.partial_response_content)
USER             self.message_tokens_sent += prompt_tokens
USER 
USER         self.message_tokens_received += completion_tokens
USER 
USER         tokens_report = f"Tokens: {format_tokens(self.message_tokens_sent)} sent"
USER 
USER         if cache_write_tokens:
USER             tokens_report += f", {format_tokens(cache_write_tokens)} cache write"
USER         if cache_hit_tokens:
USER             tokens_report += f", {format_tokens(cache_hit_tokens)} cache hit"
USER         tokens_report += f", {format_tokens(self.message_tokens_received)} received."
USER 
USER         if not self.main_model.info.get("input_cost_per_token"):
USER             self.usage_report = tokens_report
USER             return
USER 
USER         cost = 0
USER 
USER         input_cost_per_token = self.main_model.info.get("input_cost_per_token") or 0
USER         output_cost_per_token = self.main_model.info.get("output_cost_per_token") or 0
USER         input_cost_per_token_cache_hit = (
USER             self.main_model.info.get("input_cost_per_token_cache_hit") or 0
USER         )
USER 
USER         # deepseek
USER         # prompt_cache_hit_tokens + prompt_cache_miss_tokens
USER         #    == prompt_tokens == total tokens that were sent
USER         #
USER         # Anthropic
USER         # cache_creation_input_tokens + cache_read_input_tokens + prompt
USER         #    == total tokens that were
USER 
USER         if input_cost_per_token_cache_hit:
USER             # must be deepseek
USER             cost += input_cost_per_token_cache_hit * cache_hit_tokens
USER             cost += (prompt_tokens - input_cost_per_token_cache_hit) * input_cost_per_token
USER         else:
USER             # hard code the anthropic adjustments, no-ops for other models since cache_x_tokens==0
USER             cost += cache_write_tokens * input_cost_per_token * 1.25
USER             cost += cache_hit_tokens * input_cost_per_token * 0.10
USER             cost += prompt_tokens * input_cost_per_token
USER 
USER         cost += completion_tokens * output_cost_per_token
USER 
USER         self.total_cost += cost
USER         self.message_cost += cost
USER 
USER         def format_cost(value):
USER             if value == 0:
USER                 return "0.00"
USER             magnitude = abs(value)
USER             if magnitude >= 0.01:
USER                 return f"{value:.2f}"
USER             else:
USER                 return f"{value:.{max(2, 2 - int(math.log10(magnitude)))}f}"
USER 
USER         cost_report = (
USER             f"Cost: ${format_cost(self.message_cost)} message,"
USER             f" ${format_cost(self.total_cost)} session."
USER         )
USER 
USER         if self.add_cache_headers and self.stream:
USER             warning = " Use --no-stream for accurate caching costs."
USER             self.usage_report = tokens_report + "\n" + cost_report + warning
USER             return
USER 
USER         if cache_hit_tokens and cache_write_tokens:
USER             sep = "\n"
USER         else:
USER             sep = " "
USER 
USER         self.usage_report = tokens_report + sep + cost_report
USER

USER         completion_tokens = self.message_tokens_received
USER         self.event(
USER             "message_send",
USER             main_model=self.main_model,
USER             edit_format=self.edit_format,
USER             prompt_tokens=prompt_tokens,
USER             completion_tokens=completion_tokens,
USER             total_tokens=prompt_tokens + completion_tokens,
USER             cost=self.message_cost,
USER             total_cost=self.total_cost,
USER         )
USER 
USER         self.message_cost = 0.0
USER         self.message_tokens_sent = 0
USER         self.message_tokens_received = 0

USER     def get_ident_mentions(self, text):
USER         # Split the string on any character that is not alphanumeric

USER     def get_ident_filename_matches(self, idents):
USER         all_fnames = defaultdict(set)
USER         for fname in self.get_all_relative_files():
USER             # Skip empty paths or just '.'
USER             if not fname or fname == ".":
USER                 continue
USER 
USER             try:
USER                 # Handle dotfiles properly
USER                 path = Path(fname)
USER                 base = path.stem.lower()  # Use stem instead of with_suffix("").name
USER                 if len(base) >= 5:
USER                     all_fnames[base].add(fname)
USER             except ValueError:
USER                 # Skip paths that can't be processed
USER                 continue
USER 
USER         matches = set()
USER         for ident in idents:
USER             if len(ident) < 5:
USER                 continue
USER             matches.update(all_fnames[ident.lower()])
USER 
USER         return matches
USER 
USER     def get_repo_map(self, force_refresh=False):
USER         if not self.repo_map:
USER             return
USER 
USER         cur_msg_text = self.get_cur_message_text()
USER         mentioned_fnames = self.get_file_mentions(cur_msg_text)
USER         mentioned_idents = self.get_ident_mentions(cur_msg_text)
USER 
USER         mentioned_fnames.update(self.get_ident_filename_matches(mentioned_idents))
USER 
USER         all_abs_files = set(self.get_all_abs_files())
USER         repo_abs_read_only_fnames = set(self.abs_read_only_fnames) & all_abs_files
USER         chat_files = set(self.abs_fnames) | repo_abs_read_only_fnames
USER         other_files = all_abs_files - chat_files
USER 
USER         repo_content = self.repo_map.get_repo_map(
USER             chat_files,
USER             other_files,
USER             mentioned_fnames=mentioned_fnames,
USER             mentioned_idents=mentioned_idents,
USER             force_refresh=force_refresh,
USER         )
USER 
USER         # fall back to global repo map if files in chat are disjoint from rest of repo
USER         if not repo_content:
USER             repo_content = self.repo_map.get_repo_map(
USER                 set(),
USER                 all_abs_files,
USER                 mentioned_fnames=mentioned_fnames,
USER                 mentioned_idents=mentioned_idents,
USER             )
USER 
USER         # fall back to completely unhinted repo
USER         if not repo_content:
USER             repo_content = self.repo_map.get_repo_map(
USER                 set(),
USER                 all_abs_files,
USER             )
USER 
USER         return repo_content

USER     def get_images_message(self, fnames):
USER         supports_images = self.main_model.info.get("supports_vision")
USER         supports_pdfs = self.main_model.info.get("supports_pdf_input") or self.main_model.info.get(
USER             "max_pdf_size_mb"
USER         )
USER 
USER         # https://github.com/BerriAI/litellm/pull/6928
USER         supports_pdfs = supports_pdfs or "claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022" in self.main_model.name
USER 
USER         if not (supports_images or supports_pdfs):
USER             return None
USER 
USER         image_messages = []
USER         for fname in fnames:
USER             if not is_image_file(fname):
USER                 continue
USER 
USER             mime_type, _ = mimetypes.guess_type(fname)
USER             if not mime_type:
USER                 continue
USER 
USER             with open(fname, "rb") as image_file:
USER                 encoded_string = base64.b64encode(image_file.read()).decode("utf-8")
USER             image_url = f"data:{mime_type};base64,{encoded_string}"
USER             rel_fname = self.get_rel_fname(fname)
USER 
USER             if mime_type.startswith("image/") and supports_images:
USER                 image_messages += [
USER                     {"type": "text", "text": f"Image file: {rel_fname}"},
USER                     {"type": "image_url", "image_url": {"url": image_url, "detail": "high"}},
USER                 ]
USER             elif mime_type == "application/pdf" and supports_pdfs:
USER                 image_messages += [
USER                     {"type": "text", "text": f"PDF file: {rel_fname}"},
USER                     {"type": "image_url", "image_url": image_url},
USER                 ]
USER 
USER         if not image_messages:
USER             return None
USER 
USER         return {"role": "user", "content": image_messages}

USER     def run(self, with_message=None, preproc=True):
USER         try:
USER             if with_message:
USER                 self.io.user_input(with_message)
USER                 self.run_one(with_message, preproc)
USER                 return self.partial_response_content
USER             while True:
USER                 try:
USER                     if not self.io.placeholder:
USER                         self.copy_context()
USER                     user_message = self.get_input()
USER                     self.run_one(user_message, preproc)

USER         if not inp:
USER             return
USER 
USER         if self.commands.is_command(inp):
USER             return self.commands.run(inp)
USER 
USER         self.check_for_file_mentions(inp)

USER     def run_one(self, user_message, preproc):
USER         self.init_before_message()
USER 
USER         if preproc:
USER             message = self.preproc_user_input(user_message)
USER         else:
USER             message = user_message
USER 
USER         while message:
USER             self.reflected_message = None
USER             list(self.send_message(message))
USER 
USER             if not self.reflected_message:
USER                 break
USER 
USER             if self.num_reflections >= self.max_reflections:
USER                 self.io.tool_warning(f"Only {self.max_reflections} reflections allowed, stopping.")
USER                 return
USER 
USER             self.num_reflections += 1
USER             message = self.reflected_message
USER 
USER     def check_and_open_urls(self, exc, friendly_msg=None):
USER         """Check exception for URLs, offer to open in a browser, with user-friendly error msgs."""
USER         text = str(exc)
USER 
USER         if friendly_msg:
USER             self.io.tool_warning(text)
USER             self.io.tool_error(f"{friendly_msg}")
USER         else:
USER             self.io.tool_error(text)
USER 
USER         url_pattern = re.compile(r"(https?://[^\s/$.?#].[^\s]*)")
USER         urls = list(set(url_pattern.findall(text)))  # Use set to remove duplicates
USER         for url in urls:
USER             url = url.rstrip(".',\"")
USER             self.io.offer_url(url)
USER         return urls
USER 
USER     def check_for_urls(self, inp: str) -> List[str]:
USER         """Check input for URLs and offer to add them to the chat."""
USER         if not self.detect_urls:
USER             return inp
USER 
USER         url_pattern = re.compile(r"(https?://[^\s/$.?#].[^\s]*[^\s,.])")
USER         urls = list(set(url_pattern.findall(inp)))  # Use set to remove duplicates
USER         group = ConfirmGroup(urls)
USER         for url in urls:
USER             if url not in self.rejected_urls:
USER                 url = url.rstrip(".',\"")
USER                 if self.io.confirm_ask(
USER                     "Add URL to the chat?", subject=url, group=group, allow_never=True
USER                 ):
USER                     inp += "\n\n"
USER                     inp += self.commands.cmd_web(url, return_content=True)
USER                 else:
USER                     self.rejected_urls.add(url)
USER 
USER         return inp
USER

USER         if self.verbose:

USER     def summarize_worker(self):

USER     def summarize_end(self):

USER         if self.summarizing_messages == self.done_messages:
USER             self.done_messages = self.summarized_done_messages
USER         self.summarizing_messages = None
USER         self.summarized_done_messages = []

USER         if self.gpt_prompts.system_reminder:

USER         chunks.cur = list(self.cur_messages)

USER         # TODO review impact of token count on image messages

USER         cur_tokens = self.main_model.token_count(chunks.cur)

USER         if None not in (messages_tokens, reminder_tokens, cur_tokens):

USER     def warm_cache(self, chunks):
USER         if not self.add_cache_headers:
USER             return
USER         if not self.num_cache_warming_pings:
USER             return
USER 
USER         delay = 5 * 60 - 5
USER         self.next_cache_warm = time.time() + delay
USER         self.warming_pings_left = self.num_cache_warming_pings
USER         self.cache_warming_chunks = chunks
USER 
USER         if self.cache_warming_thread:
USER             return
USER 
USER         def warm_cache_worker():
USER             while True:
USER                 time.sleep(1)
USER                 if self.warming_pings_left <= 0:
USER                     continue
USER                 now = time.time()
USER                 if now < self.next_cache_warm:
USER                     continue
USER 
USER                 self.warming_pings_left -= 1
USER                 self.next_cache_warm = time.time() + delay
USER 
USER                 kwargs = dict(self.main_model.extra_params) or dict()
USER                 kwargs["max_tokens"] = 1
USER 
USER                 try:
USER                     completion = litellm.completion(
USER                         model=self.main_model.name,
USER                         messages=self.cache_warming_chunks.cacheable_messages(),
USER                         stream=False,
USER                         **kwargs,
USER                     )
USER                 except Exception as err:
USER                     self.io.tool_warning(f"Cache warming error: {str(err)}")
USER                     continue
USER 
USER                 cache_hit_tokens = getattr(
USER                     completion.usage, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens", 0
USER                 ) or getattr(completion.usage, "cache_read_input_tokens", 0)
USER 
USER                 if self.verbose:
USER                     self.io.tool_output(f"Warmed {format_tokens(cache_hit_tokens)} cached tokens.")
USER 
USER         self.cache_warming_thread = threading.Timer(0, warm_cache_worker)
USER         self.cache_warming_thread.daemon = True
USER         self.cache_warming_thread.start()
USER 
USER         return chunks
USER 
USER     def send_message(self, inp):

USER 
USER         self.cur_messages += [
USER             dict(role="user", content=inp),
USER         ]
USER 
USER         chunks = self.format_messages()
USER         messages = chunks.all_messages()
USER         self.warm_cache(chunks)
USER 
USER         if self.verbose:
USER             utils.show_messages(messages, functions=self.functions)
USER 
USER         self.multi_response_content = ""
USER         if self.show_pretty() and self.stream:
USER             self.mdstream = self.io.get_assistant_mdstream()
USER         else:
USER             self.mdstream = None
USER 
USER         retry_delay = 0.125
USER 
USER         litellm_ex = LiteLLMExceptions()
USER 
USER         self.usage_report = None
USER         exhausted = False
USER         interrupted = False

USER     def get_file_mentions(self, content):
USER         words = set(word for word in content.split())
USER 
USER         # drop sentence punctuation from the end
USER         words = set(word.rstrip(",.!;:?") for word in words)
USER 
USER         # strip away all kinds of quotes
USER         quotes = "".join(['"', "'", "`"])
USER         words = set(word.strip(quotes) for word in words)
USER 
USER         addable_rel_fnames = self.get_addable_relative_files()
USER 
USER         # Get basenames of files already in chat or read-only
USER         existing_basenames = {os.path.basename(f) for f in self.get_inchat_relative_files()} | {
USER             os.path.basename(self.get_rel_fname(f)) for f in self.abs_read_only_fnames
USER         }
USER 
USER         mentioned_rel_fnames = set()
USER         fname_to_rel_fnames = {}
USER         for rel_fname in addable_rel_fnames:
USER             # Skip files that share a basename with files already in chat
USER             if os.path.basename(rel_fname) in existing_basenames:
USER                 continue
USER 
USER             normalized_rel_fname = rel_fname.replace("\\", "/")
USER             normalized_words = set(word.replace("\\", "/") for word in words)
USER             if normalized_rel_fname in normalized_words:
USER                 mentioned_rel_fnames.add(rel_fname)
USER 
USER             fname = os.path.basename(rel_fname)
USER 
USER             # Don't add basenames that could be plain words like "run" or "make"
USER             if "/" in fname or "\\" in fname or "." in fname or "_" in fname or "-" in fname:
USER                 if fname not in fname_to_rel_fnames:
USER                     fname_to_rel_fnames[fname] = []
USER                 fname_to_rel_fnames[fname].append(rel_fname)
USER 
USER         for fname, rel_fnames in fname_to_rel_fnames.items():
USER             if len(rel_fnames) == 1 and fname in words:
USER                 mentioned_rel_fnames.add(rel_fnames[0])
USER 
USER         return mentioned_rel_fnames
USER 
USER     def check_for_file_mentions(self, content):
USER         mentioned_rel_fnames = self.get_file_mentions(content)
USER 
USER         new_mentions = mentioned_rel_fnames - self.ignore_mentions
USER 
USER         if not new_mentions:
USER             return
USER 
USER         added_fnames = []
USER         group = ConfirmGroup(new_mentions)
USER         for rel_fname in sorted(new_mentions):
USER             if self.io.confirm_ask(f"Add {rel_fname} to the chat?", group=group, allow_never=True):
USER                 self.add_rel_fname(rel_fname)
USER                 added_fnames.append(rel_fname)
USER             else:
USER                 self.ignore_mentions.add(rel_fname)
USER 
USER         if added_fnames:
USER             return prompts.added_files.format(fnames=", ".join(added_fnames))
USER

USER     def show_send_output(self, completion):
USER         if self.verbose:
USER             print(completion)
USER 
USER         if not completion.choices:
USER             self.io.tool_error(str(completion))
USER             return
USER 
USER         show_func_err = None
USER         show_content_err = None
USER         try:
USER             if completion.choices[0].message.tool_calls:
USER                 self.partial_response_function_call = (
USER                     completion.choices[0].message.tool_calls[0].function
USER                 )
USER         except AttributeError as func_err:
USER             show_func_err = func_err
USER 
USER         try:
USER             self.partial_response_content = completion.choices[0].message.content or ""
USER         except AttributeError as content_err:
USER             show_content_err = content_err
USER 
USER         resp_hash = dict(
USER             function_call=str(self.partial_response_function_call),
USER             content=self.partial_response_content,
USER         )
USER         resp_hash = hashlib.sha1(json.dumps(resp_hash, sort_keys=True).encode())
USER         self.chat_completion_response_hashes.append(resp_hash.hexdigest())
USER 
USER         if show_func_err and show_content_err:
USER             self.io.tool_error(show_func_err)
USER             self.io.tool_error(show_content_err)
USER             raise Exception("No data found in LLM response!")
USER 
USER         show_resp = self.render_incremental_response(True)
USER         self.io.assistant_output(show_resp, pretty=self.show_pretty())
USER 
USER         if (
USER             hasattr(completion.choices[0], "finish_reason")
USER             and completion.choices[0].finish_reason == "length"
USER         ):
USER             raise FinishReasonLength()
USER 
USER     def show_send_output_stream(self, completion):
USER         for chunk in completion:
USER             if len(chunk.choices) == 0:
USER                 continue
USER 
USER             if (
USER                 hasattr(chunk.choices[0], "finish_reason")
USER                 and chunk.choices[0].finish_reason == "length"
USER             ):
USER                 raise FinishReasonLength()
USER 
USER             try:
USER                 func = chunk.choices[0].delta.function_call
USER                 # dump(func)
USER                 for k, v in func.items():
USER                     if k in self.partial_response_function_call:
USER                         self.partial_response_function_call[k] += v
USER                     else:
USER                         self.partial_response_function_call[k] = v
USER             except AttributeError:
USER                 pass
USER 
USER             try:
USER                 text = chunk.choices[0].delta.content
USER                 if text:
USER                     self.partial_response_content += text
USER             except AttributeError:
USER                 text = None
USER 
USER             if self.show_pretty():
USER                 self.live_incremental_response(False)
USER             elif text:
USER                 try:
USER                     sys.stdout.write(text)
USER                 except UnicodeEncodeError:
USER                     # Safely encode and decode the text
USER                     safe_text = text.encode(sys.stdout.encoding, errors="backslashreplace").decode(
USER                         sys.stdout.encoding
USER                     )
USER                     sys.stdout.write(safe_text)
USER                 sys.stdout.flush()
USER                 yield text
USER

USER     def calculate_and_show_tokens_and_cost(self, messages, completion=None):
USER         prompt_tokens = 0
USER         completion_tokens = 0
USER         cache_hit_tokens = 0
USER         cache_write_tokens = 0
USER 
USER         if completion and hasattr(completion, "usage") and completion.usage is not None:
USER             prompt_tokens = completion.usage.prompt_tokens
USER             completion_tokens = completion.usage.completion_tokens
USER             cache_hit_tokens = getattr(completion.usage, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens", 0) or getattr(
USER                 completion.usage, "cache_read_input_tokens", 0
USER             )
USER             cache_write_tokens = getattr(completion.usage, "cache_creation_input_tokens", 0)
USER 
USER             if hasattr(completion.usage, "cache_read_input_tokens") or hasattr(
USER                 completion.usage, "cache_creation_input_tokens"
USER             ):
USER                 self.message_tokens_sent += prompt_tokens
USER                 self.message_tokens_sent += cache_write_tokens
USER             else:
USER                 self.message_tokens_sent += prompt_tokens
USER 
USER         else:
USER             prompt_tokens = self.main_model.token_count(messages)
USER             completion_tokens = self.main_model.token_count(self.partial_response_content)
USER             self.message_tokens_sent += prompt_tokens
USER 
USER         self.message_tokens_received += completion_tokens
USER 
USER         tokens_report = f"Tokens: {format_tokens(self.message_tokens_sent)} sent"
USER 
USER         if cache_write_tokens:
USER             tokens_report += f", {format_tokens(cache_write_tokens)} cache write"
USER         if cache_hit_tokens:
USER             tokens_report += f", {format_tokens(cache_hit_tokens)} cache hit"
USER         tokens_report += f", {format_tokens(self.message_tokens_received)} received."
USER 
USER         if not self.main_model.info.get("input_cost_per_token"):
USER             self.usage_report = tokens_report
USER             return
USER 
USER         cost = 0
USER 
USER         input_cost_per_token = self.main_model.info.get("input_cost_per_token") or 0
USER         output_cost_per_token = self.main_model.info.get("output_cost_per_token") or 0
USER         input_cost_per_token_cache_hit = (
USER             self.main_model.info.get("input_cost_per_token_cache_hit") or 0
USER         )
USER 
USER         # deepseek
USER         # prompt_cache_hit_tokens + prompt_cache_miss_tokens
USER         #    == prompt_tokens == total tokens that were sent
USER         #
USER         # Anthropic
USER         # cache_creation_input_tokens + cache_read_input_tokens + prompt
USER         #    == total tokens that were
USER 
USER         if input_cost_per_token_cache_hit:
USER             # must be deepseek
USER             cost += input_cost_per_token_cache_hit * cache_hit_tokens
USER             cost += (prompt_tokens - input_cost_per_token_cache_hit) * input_cost_per_token
USER         else:
USER             # hard code the anthropic adjustments, no-ops for other models since cache_x_tokens==0
USER             cost += cache_write_tokens * input_cost_per_token * 1.25
USER             cost += cache_hit_tokens * input_cost_per_token * 0.10
USER             cost += prompt_tokens * input_cost_per_token
USER 
USER         cost += completion_tokens * output_cost_per_token
USER 
USER         self.total_cost += cost
USER         self.message_cost += cost
USER 
USER         def format_cost(value):
USER             if value == 0:
USER                 return "0.00"
USER             magnitude = abs(value)
USER             if magnitude >= 0.01:
USER                 return f"{value:.2f}"
USER             else:
USER                 return f"{value:.{max(2, 2 - int(math.log10(magnitude)))}f}"
USER 
USER         cost_report = (
USER             f"Cost: ${format_cost(self.message_cost)} message,"
USER             f" ${format_cost(self.total_cost)} session."
USER         )
USER 
USER         if self.add_cache_headers and self.stream:
USER             warning = " Use --no-stream for accurate caching costs."
USER             self.usage_report = tokens_report + "\n" + cost_report + warning
USER             return
USER 
USER         if cache_hit_tokens and cache_write_tokens:
USER             sep = "\n"
USER         else:
USER             sep = " "
USER 
USER         self.usage_report = tokens_report + sep + cost_report
USER

USER         self.event(
USER             "message_send",
USER             main_model=self.main_model,
USER             edit_format=self.edit_format,
USER             prompt_tokens=prompt_tokens,
USER             completion_tokens=completion_tokens,
USER             total_tokens=prompt_tokens + completion_tokens,
USER             cost=self.message_cost,
USER             total_cost=self.total_cost,
USER         )
USER 
USER         self.message_cost = 0.0
USER         self.message_tokens_sent = 0
USER         self.message_tokens_received = 0
